4 D. SEQUENCE AND TIMING OF DISCOVERY. Unless the parties
5 stipulate or the court orders otherwise for the convenience of
6 parties and witnesses and in the interests of justice, methods of
7 discovery may be used in any sequence. The fact that a party is
8 conducting discovery, whether by deposition or otherwise, shall not
